{"author":{"id":"69a73b59e8bca0653e9174a374f9f55c998c9a49750b37bad6bd3960e96b7ca3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1717693562,"nonce":"s1VkV889Nn4nQeRmOzw7y9PPykQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc6AVEqa","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/1451#issuecomment-2153007770"},"message":"This is deliberate and not a problem.  `dandi.metadata.nwb.get_metadata()` needs to be able to accept a string, path, or `Readable` instance; it is decorated with an fscacher cache; and passing a non-string, non-path value to an fscacher-cached function simply results in the underlying function being called directly instead of using the cache:\n\nhttps://github.com/con/fscacher/blob/e52aaa00ada41a2e2868ca75644d25cd037e6f7b/src/fscacher/cache.py#L132-L138\n\n... and so everything works out.  The only reason you're seeing that error is because the underlying function failed while fscacher was handling the `TypeError`, so the latter got included in the traceback.","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1717693566,"nonce":"fCr1f0ZUCQoGRCzLl+dVYJUL1Uo=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADODBZtRc6LZc1bzwAAAAMLBaia"},"status":2}]}